Component State Requirements (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
Every interactive component MUST define and visually support:

Default
Hover
Focus-visible
Active/pressed
Disabled
Error (where applicable)
Success (where applicable)
Warning (where applicable)

No component may ship with partial state coverage.
Accessibility Standards (MANDATORY)

Keyboard navigation complete for all interactive controls
Focus ring visible on every control and variant
Icon-only controls need aria-label AND tooltip
Inputs/selects/textarea/datepickers MUST have labels
Color cannot be the only channel for meaning
Error messages adjacent and understandable
Dialogs/dropdowns maintain correct focus behavior

Routes
Public Routes

/ (landing)
/privacy
/terms
/support

Auth Routes

/login
/signup
/auth/reset-password
/auth/callback (route handler)
/auth/signout (route handler)
/auth/delete-account (route handler)

Dashboard Routes (Protected)

/dashboard
/clients
/time
/contracts
/invoices
/income

Share Routes (Public with token)

/c/[token] (contract view)
/i/[token] (invoice view)

Security Rules

Supabase RLS required for user-isolated tables
Input validated with Zod in app flows
Guest mode never relies on service-role access from client
Sensitive keys remain in environment variables
Share tokens validated server-side before rendering content
No client-side exposure of other users' data

Performance Targets

First Contentful Paint: < 1.5s
Time to Interactive: < 3s
Lighthouse score: > 90
Bundle size: monitor with next/bundle-analyzer

Testing (Vitest)

Test file naming: ComponentName.test.tsx
Coverage target: 80% (focus on business logic)
Unit tests for: utilities, validation schemas, hooks
Integration tests for: user flows, auth, data mutations

Git Workflow
Branch Naming

feat/module-name
fix/bug-description
refactor/component-name
chore/task-name

Commit Format (Conventional Commits)
type(scope): descriptionfeat(client-manager): add bulk delete functionality
fix(time-tracker): correct pause/resume state transition
refactor(invoice): extract PDF generation to utility
style(ui): align button focus states with design system
docs(readme): update setup instructions
chore(deps): upgrade React Query to v5

## Style Rules (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

1. NEVER use raw hex classes in component markup
2. NEVER use Tailwind default palette classes for product UI colors
3. ALWAYS use semantic Lumea token utilities
4. Do NOT delete or rename existing token mappings in tailwind.config.ts
5. Do NOT alter token variables in app/globals.css without explicit approval
6. Keep business logic outside presentational primitives
7. Avoid inline styles for design-system behavior
8. Avoid duplicate style systems
9. Keep component APIs stable; evolve via additive changes
10. Maintain strict TypeScript typing for all reusable components

## Pre-Merge Checklist

- [ ] No raw hex or default Tailwind color classes in component markup
- [ ] Semantic tokens used for all color decisions
- [ ] Labels, hints, and errors implemented for form controls
- [ ] Focus-visible styles verified for keyboard navigation
- [ ] Empty/loading/error states present
- [ ] Reused shared primitives where applicable
- [ ] Verified in light and dark theme
- [ ] Verified on mobile and desktop breakpoints
- [ ] TypeScript strict mode passes
- [ ] ESLint passes
- [ ] Tests passing (if applicable)

## Content and Language Standards

1. Use concise action-oriented labels
2. Use sentence case in helper and error text
3. Avoid vague errors; provide next-step guidance
4. Keep status language consistent across modules

## Common Patterns

### Date Formatting
```typescriptconst formatDate = (date: Date) =>
new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {
dateStyle: 'medium'
}).format(date);

### Currency Formatting
```typescriptconst formatCurrency = (amount: number, currency = 'USD') =>
new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', {
style: 'currency',
currency
}).format(amount);

